{"type":"message","id":"290dafa7","parentId":"776c07da","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:55:08.323Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, the user is asking which model I'm currently using. Let me check the tool_response section.\n\nIn the tools, there's a session_status tool that can show the model in use. The parameters include a 'model' field, and if set, it overrides the default. The default model listed in the runtime is 'openrouter/openrouter/free'. \n\nSince the user is asking about the current model, I should use session_status to retrieve this information. The tool will return the model name, which I can then relay to the user. \n\nWait, but if the session_status isn't called, would the default model be 'openrouter/openrouter/free'? Yes, according to the runtime info provided. However, the user might have overridden it in the session. \n\nSo, to get the accurate current model, I should trigger session_status. The response from that tool will include the model being used. Then I can inform the user accordingly. \n\nI need to make sure I call session_status with the correct parameters. The sessionKey isn't specified, but since it's the current session, maybe it's handled automatically. The model parameter in session_status allows specifying an override, but here we just want to read it. \n\nTherefore, the correct tool call is session_status without specifying a model, which will return the current model in use.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"qVJI2kFMG","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":13387,"output":642,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14029,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773989664558}}
